  "response_text": "The commercial begins with an animated Nintendo racing scene. Mario is centered in the foreground, seated in a go-kart and facing forward, wearing his bright red cap with a white “M,” red shirt, white gloves, and his black mustache. Behind him, two other Nintendo characters race in separate karts: a yellow turtle-like character on the left and Toad, with a white mushroom cap marked by red spots, on the right. Small white legal text runs along the bottom, including “No purchase necessary” and contest eligibility details. As Mario fills more of the screen, colorful block letters spelling “Domino’s” pop up across his face, followed by large multicolored numbers and letters forming “$25,000,000” and then “Nintendo Instant Win Game.” The words stack over Mario’s wide eyes, with the contest title in playful red, yellow, green, and blue lettering, while the fine print remains along the bottom.\n\nA close view then shows a person’s hands holding a rectangular Domino’s Nintendo game card against a dark background. The card has a printed panel on the left reading “Domino’s $25,000,000 Nintendo Instant Win Game,” with dense rules beneath it. On the right side of the card is a colorful illustrated game-board design with Mario near the top and a winding path. One hand uses a coin or fingernail-like motion to scratch an area on the card, revealing the instant-win play area.\n\nThe prizes are then displayed as a still-life arrangement on a tabletop: a gray Nintendo Game Boy stands upright on the left with a small game cartridge nearby, a Super Nintendo console sits in the center with purple buttons, two rounded gray controllers lie in front, and boxed or cartridge game packaging stands to the right. The scene is lit with dramatic purple and green highlights. White fine print at the bottom gives additional rules and a mail-in address for obtaining game cards or rules in certain states.\n\nThe focus shifts to food. A hot-looking pizza fills the lower left and center, covered with melted cheese and colorful toppings such as green pepper strips, onion rings, and red tomato or pepper pieces. A red Coca-Cola can stands upright behind it on the right, surrounded by vegetables and rustic food props, including peppers, garlic, tomatoes, and other produce. White rules text continues across the bottom.\n\nMario and Yoshi then appear as large animated faces against a black background. Yoshi, the green dinosaur character, is on the left with his mouth open wide in an excited expression. Mario is on the right, also open-mouthed, with his red cap, round nose, and thick mustache prominent. Both look directly outward as if reacting enthusiastically.\n\nThe food display returns, now featuring a white Domino’s paper sleeve or container on the right holding several golden bread twists. A hand reaches in from the left and another hand supports or presents the bread near the sleeve. Across the top, bright multicolored letters spell “NEW TWISTY BREAD.” The background remains packed with vegetables and warm, glossy food styling. Small white text along the bottom says it is available only at participating stores and includes pricing and tax details.\n\nA large, bold “FREE” appears in the center in red, blue, yellow, and green letters, layered over the bread, pizza, and produce. The bread twists remain on the right in the white Domino’s sleeve, while the pizza sits along the bottom edge. Finally, the “FREE” text disappears and is replaced by playful multicolored lettering reading “ALL FOR JUST 9.99,” stretched across the middle over the pizza and bread. A small Domino’s logo appears near the lower portion of the image, while the fine print continues underneath, noting that sizes and prices may vary and that the price is higher in Alaska and Hawaii.",
